member.summary:
           Compares this OSC Timetag to an object. Returns "true" if: 

- The object is another Timetag and they match; 

- The object is a 64-bit signed integer value that is equal to this Timetag's number of ticks; 

- The object is a 64-bit unsigned integer value that is equal to this Timetag's NTP timestamp value.

If both trits are "maybe", returns "maybe".
Will return "false" if at least one trit is "false" and the other is not "true".
Will return "true" if at least one trit is "true";

           Implements a basic, bare-bones version of OSC Protocol, version 1.0 - only supporting Int32, Float32, Osc-String and Osc-Blob as arguments.

           When sending out packets, arguments will be converted into one of the four supported data types:

Any integer value (both ints and uints) will be converted to int32, getting clamped accordingly; 

OSC Timetags will be clamped to an int32 value containing the integer part of the underlying NTP timestamp. 

Any floating-point value will be converted to float32; 

Any OSC Protocol-designated types (OscColor, etc) will be converted into binary OSC-blobs where possible; 

Anything else will be converted to ASCII strings.

Subscribes an event handler to a particular OSC Method. Will do one of the two things:
1. If an OSC Method already exists at the specified address, the event handler will be subscribed to it;
2. Otherwise, a new OSC Method will be created and added to this Address Space, and the event handler will be subscribed to it. If any elements of the address don't exist in this Address Space, they will be created and added too.

member.param:
The function to perform: 

-- takes one parameter (the Address Element that matches the pattern); 

-- returns a boolean (whether the function could besuccessfully performed on the provided Address Element).

The function to perform: 

-- takes one parameter (the Address Element whose name matches the pattern); 

-- returns a boolean (whether the function could besuccessfully performed on the provided Address Element).
